course_title: Special Topics: Human Health: Personalizing Nutrition

class_notes: HLTH 220 PREREQUISITE - What determines if a diet is optimal, or promotes a nutritional imbalance that affects health? This hands-on course will explore techniques and considerations for collecting and using dietary, anthropometric, biochemical, and clinical data to evaluate nutrition status of individuals and groups.
course_description: Seminar of lecture series of topics in human health. May be repeated for credit when topic varies. Credit varies from one to four hours.
